@abdullah, it was "your computer" in the sense you were using it. Physical access trumps all.

We've made a change so that any new attachments will have the correct `Cache-Control` header so that the browser knows not to cache them. We'll see about going back to fix older attachments, but the way S3 handles objects (and changes to those objects), that can be very problematic in some cases.

We'll be back in touch soon about whether this qualifies for a bounty or not, but in any case, we thank you for your report, and we have added you to our Hall of Fame.

@reed  Hi , Any update for bounty decision . 

And can I ask for Hackerone hoodie if you don't mind .

Thanks

@abdullah, 

After careful consideration, we've decided to not award a bounty for this issue, as in order for an attacker to gain anything from this, they must violate the [Immutable Law of Security #3](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc722487.aspx#EIAA): "If a bad guy has unrestricted physical access to your computer, it's not your computer anymore". We have added you to our thanks page as a token of appreciation for submitting this to us.

We look forward to future submissions from you. Happy hacking!
